<br>
Heres why:<br>
No Levi... I love levi + jboots, great for kiting in CS/TD and travel in many other places.  Sure Horses have safefall, but what good does that do me when i run over water to round stuff up?<br>
Horses drop the second you zone in doors.  JBoots you can click right before you zone in and have the speed for a good while longer.  <br>
JBoots are instant, horses have a slight delay.  <br>
<br>
I say go for JBoots.<br>
If you have cash left over and want a horse for mana regen (regen while running/standing/casting) get a crappy 8K one?  <br>
<br>
My thoughts <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uoxoxoxoxox.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oxoxo Xoxox</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalRainbow.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/27/01 10:08:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=254.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www2.swmed.edu/libraryis/eq/wizsig4.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> jboots or better yet, innate run speed alt xp points</span><hr size=1> Horses are not for soloing/kiting.  What they are for is grouping outdoors and getting places fast.  The Horses kick major ass tho because while grouped outdoors(or in dungeons considered outdoors) you are always considered medding even while moving or casting on one.  <br>
<br>
The 110k horse is a waste of money as well as the 10k horse.  I say this because the 60k horse goes so fast who really cares if your a tad faster. For almost double the price when no one can tell by looking at it? I dont think so.  The 10k horse is slower than jboots and if your gonna spend massive plats on a horse at least get some good speed out of it.<br>
<br>
10k horse - do not buy<br>
30k horse - great horse<br>
60k horse - best horse<br>
110 horse - do not buy unless you like flushing money down the toilet.<br>
<br>
as for comparing Jboots and horses.  forget both if you want a solo/kiting solution.  Get innate run speed x3 alt xp advancement and you will always run at jboots speed indoors and out.  Save you plats for a nice horse 30k/60k<br>
<br>
P.S.  The Horse's safe fall skill is so high you can ride off the Kelethin lifts and only take 200ish damage, anything lower than that and you dont take damage at all <p><b><a href='http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=3693'>Oxoxo Xoxox</a></b> lvl 56 Evoker<BR>

